-- Zamil Tumbles Most Since May in Riyadh Trading After Profit Declined 41%
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2010-10-18T08:53:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-18/zamil-tumbles-most-since-may-in-riyadh-trading-after-profit-declined-41-.html
Zamil Industrial Investment Co.
declined the most since May after the Saudi maker of steel and
steel products said thrid-quarter profit fell 41 percent after
sales and profit margins dropped.  The shares slumped 8.2 percent, the most since May 25, to
40.4 riyals at 11:48 a.m. in Riyadh.  Net income tumbled to 31.7 million riyals ($8.5 million)
from 53.8 million riyals in the year-earlier period.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
